description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking aClinical and Information Governance Officer to join the Omnes Healthcare Family; become part of a company that makes a difference.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Salary: £23,300 per hour, depending on skills and experience&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hours: 40 Hours&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Location: Remotely and on occations our Head Office&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Up to 1 year fixed-term contract&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;em&gt;We have fully COVID compliant infection control policies in place.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Omnes Healthcare Limited are operating within the NHS to provide personalised, quality healthcare services and have been doing so since 2006. We aim to develop supportive, genuine relationships with every patient, physician, nurse and healthcare professional that we come into contact with. We believe each patient is unique and deserves treatment that is both effective, heartfelt and has a positive outcome on their well-being.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you join us, you&#39;ll be part of something special–an innovative and rapidly growing organisation where we know that the finest patient care comes from empowering our teams to be the very best at what they do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is the purpose of the position?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Omnes Healthcare are looking for a self-motivatedClinical and Information Governance Officer. The selected applicant will have experience with Information Governance and General Governance to work within the Governance Team; supporting the completion of IG requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are the key responsibilities?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administrate on a day-to-day basis, the governance structure and decision making framework, ensuring all necessary information is provided to the Head of Governance in a timely manner to ensure they can report to the Board effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide a professional administration service (including prepare agenda, reports, action lists, minutes, arrange meetings, liaise with Service/Practice Managers on relevant issues) to ensure compliance with statutory governance rules and regulations, procedures and practices, and the production and quality of governance reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake appropriate post-meeting action to ensure implementation of decisions arising from meetings serviced by the post holder or as required by the Head of Governance or Managing Director and ensure an appropriate diarised forward plan for the work of the Head of Governance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What do you need to join the Omnes Healthcare Family?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in a Governance of Information Governance position, preferably within the NHS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Honest, clear-thinker and able to develop relationships and local networks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of legislative governance systems such as CQC/Monitor/HSE/IG Toolkit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will Omnes Healthcare offer you in return?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 days holiday plus bank holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An extra day off to celebrate your birthday&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Discount&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And other benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Apply today if you want to make a difference.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We believe in innovation; we believe in listening to everyone; we believe in providing quality service; and we believe our employees will help us achieve our mission.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please be aware that all communications about this vacancy will be received to you via email. Always check your mail box and junk mail folders and provide a UK mobile number if available.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
